remarks.text:
Erd\H{o}s \cite{Er81l} proved this is true under either of the stronger assumptions that
{UL}
{LI} $a_{n+1}-a_n\to \infty$ or {/LI}
{LI} $a_n \gg n\sqrt{\log n\log\log n}$.{/LI}
{/UL}
Erd\H{o}s and Graham speculate that the condition $\limsup a_{n+1}-a_n=\infty$ is not sufficient, but know of no example.

In \cite{Va99} this is asked with $a_n/n\to \infty$ replaced by $a_{n+1}-a_n\to \infty$, which as above was proved by Erd\H{o}s in \cite{Er81l}.
